h3. Problem Definition
Users who don't have the global permission Share dashboards and filters are not displayed with a message when changing an existing filter sharing setting. 
When saving the change, Jira simply doesn't do anything as like the button wasn't working.

The only hint about the issue is that in the network tab of the browser console, we can see a 400 status code from a PUT towards https://instancename.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/filter/filterID and the response is:
{code}
{"errorMessages":[],"errors":{"shares":"You do not have permission to share. All shares are invalid.","shares_delegated":"The user '********' does not have permission to share. The owner has not been changed."}}
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
Add warning message in the UI to notify the user that they lack the global permission just like the request already does in the console.

it would be nice to be able to do the following

{code:java}

{{issue.subtasks.duedate.max}}
{{issue.versions.name.join(" &")}}
{{issue.fields.Score.avg}}
{code}

alternative format:


{code:java}
{{issue.subtasks.max.duedate}}
{{issue.versions.join(" &").name}}
{code}

First is more natural, second may easier to implement.

h3. Issue Summary
Images and attachments are failing to load in the new issue view. 
An investigation has shown this is due to the wrong media attachment ID being added to the ADF body during the conversion from wiki markup to ADF.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 _Unable to reliably reproduce_
This can be verified using a GraphQL query to check the comment body by navigating to:
* https://<sitename>.atlassian.net/rest/graphql/latest/

And the running the below GraphQL query:
{code:json}
{
  issueComments(issueIdOrKey:"LC-2517")
  {
    nodes{
      bodyAdf
    }
    nodes{
      renderedBody
    }
  }
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The media attachment ID's in both the {{renderdBody}} and {{bodyADF}} should be the same.

h3. Actual Results
The {{bodyADF}} contains attachment ID's that are not related to the issue.


h3. Workaround
Please contact Atlassian support who can help run a workaround to fix this issue.

